  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Kep Farm for People with Disabilities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Kep Farm - social business was developed in response to the need for a safe environment for people with disabilities (PWD) who have outgrown alternative care institutions as they turn 18 years old. Due to the societal stigmas embedded in karma, it is believed a disability is a form of punishment for a crime committed in a past life. Therefore, PWD face persistent discrimination in Cambodian society. The farm offers skill-based training and life-skill training to empower every beneficiary.</narrative>
  </description>
